<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-12-15T04:44:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-12-15T04:44:00-05:00" n="498" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d498">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">882.01/65: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Walton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-12-15T09:00:00-00:44">December 15, 1936—9
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 11:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>44. Confidentially and reliably informed Great Britain will recognize
                            Liberia Wednesday, December 16th, at 11 a.m., when British colleague
                            presents credentials.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Walton</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>